Name: Diiodohydroxyquinoline
Information: Diiodohydroxyquinoline (Iodoquinol) is a topical therapeutic agent,a quinoline derivative, with satisfactory antibacterial properties.

Name: Sulfabenzamide
Information: Sulfabenzamide (Sultrin, N-Sulfanilylbenzamide) is an antibacterial/antimicrobial which also exhibit their antitumor effects through multiple mechanisms including inhibition of membrane bound carbonic anhydrases, prevention of microtubule assembly, cell cycle arrest, and inhibition of angiogenesis.

Name: Succinylsulfathiazole
Information: Succinylsulfathiazole (Succinylsulphathiazole), a sulfonamide, is an antibiotic.

Name: Nitroxoline
Information: Nitroxoline (8-Hydroxy-5-nitroquinoline, 5-nitroquinolin-8-ol, 5-Nitro-8-quinolinol, 5-Nitro-8-hydroxyquinoline) is a urinary antibacterial agent active against susceptible gram-positive and gram-negative organisms commonly found in urinary tract infections. Nitroxoline impairs tumor progression in vitro and in vivo by inhibiting cathepsin B activity.

Name: Cephalothin sodium
Information: Cephalothin (Cefalotin, Cephalotin) sodium is a semisynthetic, beta-lactam, first-generation cephalosporin antibiotic with bactericidal activity. Cephalothin binds to and inactivates penicillin-binding proteins (PBP) located on the inner membrane of the bacterial cell wall.

Name: Cefazolin Sodium
Information: Cefazolin Sodium (cefazoline, cephazolin, Ancef) is a semisynthetic cephalosporin analog with broad-spectrum antibiotic action due to inhibition of bacterial cell wall synthesis. It attains high serum levels and is excreted quickly via the urine.

Name: Cefixime
Information: Cefixime (Cefixima, Cefiximum, Cephoral, Cefspan, FR-17027, FK-027, CL-284635) is an antibiotic useful for the treatment of a number of bacterial infections. It is a third generation cephalosporin.
Synonyms: Cefixima, Cefiximum, Cephoral, Cefspan, FR-17027, FK-027, CL-284635

Name: Clioquinol
Information: Clioquinol is an orally bioavailable, lipophilic, copper-binding, halogenated 8-hydroxyquinoline with antifungal, antiparasitic and potential antitumor activities.

Name: Levofloxacin hydrate
Information: Levofloxacin (Levaquin, Tavanic, Quixin, Iquix, Cravit) is a broad-spectrum, third-generation fluoroquinolone antibiotic and optically active L-isomer of ofloxacin with antibacterial activity. It acts by inhibiting DNA gyrase (bacterial topoisomerase II).
Synonyms: Levofloxacin hemihydrate, Levaquin hydrate, Tavanic hydrate, Quixin hydrate, Iquix hydrate, Cravit hydrate

Name: Dapson
Information: Dapson (Dapsone, 4,4′-Diaminodiphenyl sulfone, 4,4′-Sulfonyldianiline, 4-Aminophenyl sulfone, Bis(4-aminophenyl) sulfone, DDS), also known as diaminodiphenyl sulfone (DDS), is an antibiotic commonly used in combination with rifampicin and clofazimine for the treatment of leprosy.
Synonyms: Dapsone, 4,4′-Diaminodiphenyl sulfone, 4,4′-Sulfonyldianiline, 4-Aminophenyl sulfone, Bis(4-aminophenyl) sulfone, DDS

Name: Cefuroxime sodium
Information: Cefuroxime Sodium is a cephalosporin effective against gram-positive and gram-negative bacteria with resistance to β-lactamase.

Name: Sodium sulfadiazine
Information: Sodium Sulfadiazine (Sulfadiazin-natrium) is a sodium salt form of sulfadiazine, an intermediate-acting bacteriostatic, synthetic sulfanilamide derivative.

Name: Tedizolid Phosphate
Information: Tedizolid (TR-701FA) is an oxazolidinone-class antibiotic. Tedizolid phosphate is a phosphate ester prodrug of the active compound tedizolid.

Name: Cefmenoxime hydrochloride
Information: Cefmenoxime (SCE-1365), a potent inhibitor of Enterobacteriaceae, is a cephalosporin antibiotic that is administered intravenously or intramuscularly.

Name: Fusidate Sodium
Information: Fusidate Sodium (Fucidin, SQ-16360) is a sodium salt form of fusidic acid, a bacteriostatic antibiotic derived from the fungus Fusidium coccineum and used as a topical medication to treat skin infections.

Name: Cefotaxime
Information: Cefotaxime(HR-756) is a third-generation cephalosporin antibiotic and has broad spectrum activity against Gram positive and Gram negative bacteria.

Name: Sulfacetamide sodium salt hydrate
Information: Sulfacetamide is a sulfonamide antibiotic that blocks the synthesis of dihydrofolic acid by inhibiting the enzyme dihydropteroate synthase(DHPS) with IC50 of 9.5 μM. Sulfacetamide is a competitive inhibitor of bacterial para-aminobenzoic acid (PABA), which is required for bacterial synthesis of folic acid.

Name: Benzyl isothiocyanate
Information: Benzyl isothiocyanate (BITC, Benzoylthiocarbimide, Isothiocyanic Acid Benzoyl Ester) is an isothiocyanate originally found in cruciferous vegetables that exhibits immunomodulatory, anti-parasitic, antibiotic, antioxidative, anti-atherosclerotic, anti-angiogenic, anti-metastatic, anticancer chemotherapeutic, and chemopreventive activities.

Name: Phloracetophenone
Information: Phloracetophenone, or 2,4,6-trihydroxyacetophenone (THA), the aglycone component of phloracetophenone glucoside, is a naturally occurring compound obtained from the rhizome of Curcuma comosa (Family Zingiberaceae). Phloracetophenone can stimulate CYP7A1 activity. Phloracetophenone induces cholestasis in rats mediated through Mrp2.

Name: Carboxine
Information: Carboxin (Carbathiin, Vitavax, Kisvax) is a systemic agricultural fungicide and seed protectant. Carboxin inhibits succinate dehydrogenaseactivity .

Name: Ceftizoxime
Information: Ceftizoxime is a semisynthetic cephalosporin antibiotic which can be administered intravenously or by suppository. It is highly resistant to a broad spectrum of beta-lactamases and is active against a wide range of both aerobic and anaerobic gram-positive and gram-negative organisms.

Name: Cefuroxime axetil
Information: Cefuroxime axetil, a prodrug of the cephalosporin cefuroxime, is a second generation oral cephalosporin antibiotic with in vitro antibacterial activity against several gram-positive and gram-negative organisms.

Name: Cefoxitin sodium
Information: Cefoxitin Sodium is the sodium salt form of cefoxitin, a beta-lactam, second-generation cephalosporin antibiotic with bactericidal activity.

Name: Cefcapene Pivoxil Hydrochloride
Information: Cefcapene Pivoxil is the pivalate ester prodrug form of cefcapene, a semi-synthetic third-generation cephalosporin with antibacterial activity.

Name: Meropenem Trihydrate
Information: Meropenem is a broad-spectrum antibacterial agent of the carbapenem family with a broad spectrum of in vitro activity against Gram-positive and Gram-negative pathogens.

Name: Faropenem Sodium
Information: Faropenem sodium is an orally active beta-lactam antibiotic that has been used in trials studying the treatment of Tuberculosis, Pulmonary Tuberculosis, and Community Acquired Pneumonia.

Name: Dalbavancin
Information: Dalbavancin (Zeven, BI 397, MDL 63397) is a lipoglycopeptide antibiotic that has bactericidal activity against Gram-positive bacteria including various staphylococci.

Name: Flucloxacillin sodium
Information: Flucloxacillin sodium (Floxacillin sodium) is the sodium salt of flucloxacillin, a penicillin antibiotic used to treat bacterial infections.

Name: Bedaquiline fumarate
Information: Bedaquiline fumarate (TMC-207), an oral diarylquinoline,  is a bactericidal antimycobacterial drug. It is a proton-translocating ATP synthetase inhibitor.

Name: Cefetamet pivoxil hydrochloride
Information: Cefetamet pivoxil hydrochloride is the hydrochloride salt form of cefetamet pivoxil, which is an oral third-generation cephalosporin antibiotic.

Name: Nicarbazin
Information: Nicarbazin, an effective anticoccidial, is also a wide-spectrum anti-parasitic drug.

Name: Sulfamethoxazole sodium
Information: Sulfamethoxazole sodium is an antibiotic used for bacterial infections.

Name: Cefodizime Sodium
Information: Cefodizime Sodium, a third generation cephalosporin antibiotic, has broad-spectrum activity and is stable to most beta-lactamases.

Name: Cefazedone
Information: Cefazedone (Refosporen, Cefazedonum) is a semisynthetic first-generation cephalosporin with antibacterial activity.

Name: Cephapirin Benzathine
Information: Cephapirin Benzathine is the benzathine salt form of cephapirin, which is a semisynthetic, broad-spectrum, first-generation cephalosporin with antibacterial activity.

Name: Cefathiamidine
Information: Cefathiamidine is the first generation of cephalosporin antibacterial used for the treatment of respiratory, liver, five senses, urinary tract infections, endocarditis and sepsis.

Name: Taurolidine
Information: Taurolidine (Taurolin, Tauroline, Tauroflex) is a synthetic broad-spectrum antibiotic with antibacterial, anticoagulant and potential antiangiogenic activities.

Name: Sulfalozine sodium
Information: Sulfalozine sodium (Sulfaclozine sodium, Sulfachlopryrazine sodium) is an antiprotozoal useful in coccidiosis research.

Name: Farnesol
Information: Farnesol is a natural sesquiterpene alcohol that is potent in treating antimetabolic disorders, anti-inflammation, showing antioxidant, anticancer, and antibiotic effects.
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.

Name: Purpurin
Information: Purpurin (1,2,4-Trihydroxyanthraquinone, Hydroxylizaric acid, Verantin) is one of the natural colorants extracted from madder roots and other Rubiaceae family plants. It exhibits anti-angiogenic, antifungal, antibiotic, and antioxidative activities. Purpurin strongly inhibits the activities of CYP1A1, CYP1A2 and CYP1B1.

Name: Buparvaquone
Information: Buparvaquone (Butalex) is a second-generation hydroxynaphthoquinone related to parvaquone, with novel features that make it a promising compound for the therapy and prophylaxis of all forms of theileriosis.

Name: Sulfalene (SMPZ)
Information: Sulfalene (SMPZ, Butadiene sulfone, 3-Sulfolene) is a cyclic organic chemical used as a versatile synthetic intermediate.

Name: Azathramycin
Information: Azathramycin (Azaerythromycin A, Azaerythromycin) is a macrolide antibiotic containing cladinose.

Name: 2,2':5',2''-Terthiophene
Information: 2,2':5',2''-Terthiophene is a natural product occurring in marigold which shows UV-enhanced antibiotic activity.

Name: Sorbic acid
Information: Sorbic acid (2,4-Hexadienoic acid) is a naturally occurring compound that originated from the unripe berries of the Rowan Tree. It inhibits various bacteria, including sporeformers, at various stages of their life cycle (germination, outgrowth and cell division).

Name: Tiamulin fumarate
Information: Tiamulin fumarate is a semisynthetic pleuromutilin antibiotic that binds to the ribosomal peptidyl transferase centre and inhibits protein synthesis.

Name: Tavaborole (AN-2690)
Information: Tavaborole (AN-2690) is a boron-containing small molecule with broad spectrum antifungal activity.

Name: Avermectin B1
Information: Avermectin B1 (Abamectin) is a widely used insecticide and anthelmintic.

Name: Cefotiam hydrochloride
Information: Cefotiam hydrochloride (Halospor, Pansporin, Pansporine) is the hydrochloride salt form of cefotiam and has a broad spectrum of activity against both gram-positive and gram-negative microorganisms.

Name: Delamanid
Information: Delamanid (OPC-67683) is a new anti-tuberculosis drug with an excellent intracellular bactericidal activity and a high accumulation rate.

Name: Phenazine methosulfate
Information: Phenazine methosulfate (N-Methylphenazonium methosulfate, 5-Methylphenazinium methyl sulfate) is widely used as an intermediate electron carrier for coupling the production of NADH or NADPH to the reduction of tetrazolium salts to coloured formazans.

Name: Tiamulin
Information: Tiamulin is a semisynthetic pleuromutilin antibiotic that binds to the ribosomal peptidyl transferase centre and inhibits protein synthesis. Tiamulin has sustained antibacterial activity against specified bacterial species and rapidly growing and fastidious animal pathogens.

Name: Difloxacin hydrochloride
Information: Difloxacin is a second-generation, synthetic fluoroquinolone antimicrobial antibiotic used in veterinary medicine.

Name: Rifamycin sodium salt
Information: Rifamycin sodium is an antibacterial drug used for treatment of mycobacterium infections.

Name: Milbemycin Oxime
Information: Milbemycin Oxime is a broad spectrum anti-parasitic drug that is active against worms (anthelmintic) and mites (miticide).

Name: Ganciclovir sodium
Information: Ganciclovir Sodium (RS-21592, Cytovene IV, BW 759, 2'-Nor-2'-deoxyguanosine) is the sodium salt form of ganciclovir, a synthetic, antiviral, purine nucleoside analog with antiviral activity, especially against cytomegalovirus (CMV).
Synonyms: RS-21592 sodium, Cytovene IV sodium, BW 759 sodium, 2'-Nor-2'-deoxyguanosine sodium

Name: Mupirocin calcium
Information: Mupirocin Calcium (Pseudomonic acid A) is the calcium salt form of mupirocin, a natural crotonic acid derivative extracted from Pseudomonas fluorescens,which inhibits bacterial protein synthesis and is used as an antibiotic.

Name: Ceforanide
Information: Ceforanide is a new cephalosporin with antibacterial activity and has a longer elimination half-life than any currently available cephalosporin.

Name: Maduramycin Ammonium
Information: Maduramicin, which could be isolated from the actinomycete Actinomadura rubra, is an antiprotozoal agent used in veterinary medicine to prevent coccidiosis.

Name: SulfadiMethoxine sodium
Information: Sulfadimethoxine (Sulfadimethoxydiazine) is a long-lasting sulfonamide antimicrobial agent used to treat many infections including treatment of respiratory, urinary tract, enteric, and soft tissue infections.

Name: Tylosin
Information: Tylosin (Fradizine, Tylocine, Tylosine, Tylosin A) is a macrolide-class broad spectrum antibiotic that's used in veterinary medicine to treat felines, canines and livestock.

Name: Doramectin
Information: Doramectin (Cyclohexylavermectin B1, Dectomax) is a macrocyclic lactone derivative of ivermectin, an anthelmintic that potentiates glutamate- and GABA-gated chloride channel opening in nematodes. It is used for the treatment and control of internal parasitosis, ticks and mange.

Name: Doxycycline
Information: Doxycycline (Vibramycin, Doxytetracycline, Doxiciclina, Doxycyclinum) is an antibiotic that is used in the treatment of a number of types of infections caused by bacteria and protozoa. Doxycycline is also a nonspecific matrix metalloproteinase (MMP) inhibitor.

Name: Chlorotetracycline
Information: Chlortetracycline is a tetracycline antibiotic and commonly used to treat conjunctivitis in cats.

Name: Acetylisovaleryltylosin Tartrate
Information: Acetylisovaleryltylosin tartrate (AK105039) is an antimicrobial of the macrolide group with antibacterial activity against Gram-positive bacteria.

Name: Quinocetone
Information: Quinocetone is a novel veterinary chemicals that is also bacteriocide and potential anti-tumor agent.

Name: Benzylpenicillin potassium
Information: Benzylpenicillin potassium (Penicillin G potassium) is the potassium salt form of penicillin G, a broad-spectrum penicillin antibiotic.

Name: Ciprofloxacin hydrochloride hydrate
Information: Ciprofloxacin Hydrochloride (Ciloxan, Ceprimax, Oftacilox,Bay-09867 hydrochloride hydrate) is the hydrochloride salt form of ciprofloxacin, which is an antibiotic used to treat a number of bacterial infections.

Name: Enoxacin Sesquihydrate
Information: Enoxacin sesquihydrate (Enoxacin hydrate) is a broad-spectrum 6-fluoronaphthyridinone antibacterial agent.

Name: Sulfamethazine Sodium Salt
Information: Sulfamethazine (Sulfadimethyldiazine) is a sulfanilamide anti-infective agent used in the lifestock industry.

Name: 4-Aminosalicylic acid
Information: 4-Aminosalicylic acid (Para-aminosalicylic acid, Aminosalicylic acid, 4-aminosalicylate) is an antitubercular agent with bacteriostatic activity against Mycobacterium tuberculosis.

Name: Erythromycin thiocyanate
Information: Erythromycin is a macrolide antibiotic that inhibits bacterial protein synthesis by binding to bacterial 50S ribosomal subunits and inhibits peptidyl transferase activity and interferes with translocation of amino acids during translation and assembly of proteins.

Name: UNC-926
Information: UNC-926 is a L3MBTL1 domain inhibitor with Kd value of 3.9 μM for binding with the MBT domain of the L3MBTL1 protein.

Name: Solithromycin
Information: Solithromycin (CEM-101, OP-1068), belonging to the well-known class of macrolide antibiotics that also includes azithromycin, is a potent bacterial protein synthesis inhibitor.

Name: Tedizolid (TR-700)
Information: Tedizolid(TR-700) is an oxazolidinone-class antibiotic prodrug used for the treatment of acute bacterial skin and skin structure infections caused by susceptible isolates of several Gram-positive bacteria.

Name: Ceftezole
Information: Ceftezole (Celoslin, Falomesin) is a semi-synthetic first-generation cephalosporin with antibacterial activity.

Name: sulfaisodimidine
Information: Sulfaisodimidine (Sulfamethin) is a sulfonamide antibacterial.

Name: Cephalotin acid
Information: Cephalotin acid (Cephalothin, Cefalotin, Cephalothinum) is a cephalosporin antibiotic.

Name: Lincomycin Hydrochloride Monohydrate
Information: Lincomycin hydrochloride monohydrate is a narrow-spectrum antibiotic used in the treatment of staphylococcal, streptococcal, and Bacteroides fragilis infections.

Name: Vidarabine monohydrate
Information: Vidarabine (Spongoadenosine, Vira-A) is a nucleoside antibiotic with antiviral acitivity that interferes with the synthesis of viral DNA. It is used to treat herpes simplex and varicella zoster viruses.

Name: Amoxicillin trihydrate
Information: Amoxicillin (Amoxil, Amoxipen, Moxaline) is a broad-spectrum, semisynthetic aminopenicillin antibiotic with bactericidal activity.
Synonyms: Amoxil trihydrate, Amoxipen trihydrate, Moxaline trihydrate

Name: Tosufloxacin p-Toluenesulfonate Hydrate
Information: Tosufloxacin (T-3262) is a fluoroquinolone antibiotic that is used to treat susceptible infections.
Synonyms: Tosufloxacin Tosylate Hydrate, T-3262 Tosylate Hydrate

Name: Gamithromycin
Information: Gamithromycin (ML-1709460) is a new macrolide antibiotic that is only registered for use in cattle to treat respiratory disorders such as bovine respiratory disease.

Name: Ceftezole sodium
Information: Ceftezole Sodium (Celoslin sodium, Falomesin sodium) is the sodium salt form of ceftezole, a semi-synthetic first-generation cephalosporin with antibacterial activity.

Name: Cefquinome sulfate
Information: Cefquinome sulphate is a veterinary, parenteral, and fourth-generation cephalosporin. Its antimicrobial potency and extensive antibacterial spectrum result from the introduction of a methoxyimino-aminothiazolyl moiety into the acyl side chain.

Name: Sulbenicillin Sodium
Information: Sulbenicillin Sodium (Sulfocillin, Sulfobenzylpenicillin) is the sodium salt of sulbenicillin, which is a penicillin antibiotic.

Name: Cefpodoxime proxetil
Information: Cefpodoxime Proxetil is a third generation semi-synthetic cephalosporin and a beta-lactam antibiotic with bactericidal activity.

Name: Cefmetazole sodium
Information: Cefmetazole sodium is a semisynthetic cephamycin antibiotic with a broad spectrum of activity against both gram-positive and gram-negative microorganisms.

Name: Cefminox Sodium
Information: Cefminox Sodium (Meicelin, MT-141) is the sodium salt form of cefminox, a semi-synthetic, second-generation, beta-lactamase-stable cephalosporin with antibacterial activity.

Name: Cefpiramide sodium
Information: Cefpiramide sodium (CPMS, SM-1652,wy-44635) is an anionic β-lactam antibiotic. It exhibits antibacterial activity against gram-positive and gram-negative bacteria, in particular, to Pseudomonas aeruginosa, which can result in achronic life-threatening infection in the lungs of cystic fibrosis patients.

Name: Ceftiofur
Information: Ceftiofur is a semisynthetic, beta-lactamase-stable, broad-spectrum cephalosporin with antibacterial activity.

Name: Chlorhexidine
Information: Chlorhexidine is a disinfectant and topical anti-infective agent that is active against Gram-positive and Gram-negative organisms, facultative anaerobes, aerobes, and yeasts.

Name: Sultamicillin Tosylate
Information: Sultamicillin Tosylate is the tosylate salt of the double ester of sulbactam plus ampicillin. Sulbactam is a semisynthetic beta-lactamase inhibitor which, in combination with ampicillin, extends the antibacterial activity of the latter to include some beta-lactamase-producing strains of bacteria that would otherwise be resistant.

Name: Chloramphenicol sodium succinate
Information: Chloramphenicol Sodium Succinate is the sodium succinate salt form of chloramphenicol, a nitrobenzene derivate and broad-spectrum antibiotic with antibacterial activity.

Name: Sultamicillin
Information: Sultamicillin is a newly developed antibiotic in which ampicillin and the β-lactamase inhibitor sulbactam are linked as an ester.

Name: Clindamycin alcoholate
Information: Clindamycin alcoholate is a crystallizable compound of Clindamycin with alcohol. Clindamycin is a semisynthetic lincosamide antibiotic that inhibits bacterial protein synthesis by binding to bacterial 50S ribosomal subunits.

Name: Fluoroquinolonic Acid
Information: Fluoroquinolonic Acid (Ciprofloxacin Impurity A, Q-Acid) is an antibiotic and antimicrobial agent.

Name: Berberine Sulfate
Information: Berberine sulfate (Umbellatine), an alkaloid extracted from several plants, possesses antimicrobial activity against a wide variety of microorganisms including Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria, fungi, and protozoa.

Name: Pivmecillinam hydrochloride
Information: Pivmecillinam is a β-lactam antibiotic and a prodrug of mecillinam. It has selective activity against Gram-negative bacteria and is used primarily in the treatment of lower urinary tract infections.

Name: Cefoperazone sodium
Information: Cefoperazone Sodium(CP 52640-2) is the sodium salt form of cefoperazone, which is a semi-synthetic, broad-spectrum, beta-lactamase resistant antibiotic with bactericidal activity.

Name: Lomefloxacin
Information: Lomefloxacin(SC47111A) is a fluoroquinolone antibiotic used to treat bacterial infections.

Name: Econazole
Information: Econazole is a broad spectrum antimycotic with some action against Gram positive bacteria.

Name: Penicillin G Procaine
Information: Procaine benzylpenicillin (Procaine benzylpenicillin,PGP), also known as Procaine benzylpenicillin, is an antibiotic useful for the treatment of a number of bacterial infections.

Name: Doripenem
Information: Doripenem(S 4661) is a new parenteral carbapenem antibiotic with broad-spectrum activity against gram-negative and gram-positive pathogens.

Name: Moxifloxacin
Information: Moxifloxacin is an antibiotic used to treat a number of bacterial infections, active against Mycobacterium tuberculosis in vitro.

Name: Dimetridazole
Information: Dimetridazole is an anti-fungal and anti-protozoal used for the control of infection in pigs, poultry, turkeys, game birds, pigeons and other caged birds.

Name: Sulfacetamide
Information: Sulfacetamide (Acetosulfamine) is a synthetic sulfanylacetamide derivative with bacteriostatic activity. It is an anti-infective agent that is used topically to treat skin infections and orally for urinary tract infections.

Name: Kasugamycin hydrochloride
Target: Antineoplastic and Immunosuppressive Antibiotics,Fungal,Selection Antibiotics for Transfected Cell
Information: Kasugamycin is an aminoglycosidic antibiotic isolated from Streptomyces kasugaensis, showing broad-spectrum anti-fungal activity against yeast and various fungus species.
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.

Name: Midecamycin
Information: Midecamycin (Espinomycin A, Medecamycin A1, Platenomycin B1, Rubimycin, Turimycin P3) is a naturally occuring macrolide antibiotic that acts by inhibiting bacterial protein synthesis.
Synonyms: Espinomycin A, Medecamycin A1, Platenomycin B1, Rubimycin, Turimycin P3

Name: Tilmicosin phosphate
Information: Tilmicosin phosphate is a macrolide antibiotic that is used to treat cattle for pathogens that cause Bovine Respiratory Disease.

Name: Cilastatin
Information: Cilastatin(MK0791) is a renal dehydropeptidase-I and leukotriene D4 dipeptidase inhibitor.

Name: Bedaquiline
Information: Bedaquiline (TMC-207, R207910), a diarylquinoline, binds to subunit c of mycobacterial ATP synthase and inhibits its activity. It is highly selective for mycobacterial ATP synthase enzyme compared to homologous eukaryotic enzyme (Selectivity Index >20 000).

Name: Cefotiam Hexetil Hydrochloride
Information: Cefotiam Hexetil Hydrochloride is the hydrochloride salt of cefotiam hexetil. Cefotiam is a semi-synthetic, beta-lactam cephalosporin antibiotic with antibacterial activity.

Name: Cefozopran hydrochloride
Information: Cefozopran Hydrochloride is the hydrochloride salt form of cefozopran, a semi-synthetic, broad-spectrum, fourth-generation cephalosporin with antibacterial activity.

Name: Ertapenem sodium
Information: Ertapenem Sodium (MK826) is the sodium salt of ertapenem, a long-acting, broad-spectrum antibiotic of β-lactam subclass.

Name: Phthalylsulfathiazole
Information: Phthalylsulfathiazole (Sulfathalidine) is a broad-spectrum antimicrobial that can treat different types of infections including intestinal.

Name: Ceftizoxime sodium
Information: Ceftizoxime sodium(SKF-88373) is a semisynthetic cephalosporin antibiotic that is highly resistant to a broad spectrum of beta-lactamases and is active against a wide range of both aerobic and anaerobic gram-positive and gram-negative organisms.

Name: Benzathine penicilline
Information: Benzathine penicilline (Benzathine penicillin G) is an antibiotic useful for the treatment of a number of bacterial infections.

Name: Spiramycin I
Information: Spiramycin I (Foromacidin A) is a main component of spiramycin, which is a macrolide antimicrobial agent with broad spectrum antibiotic activity.

Name: Citric acid
Information: Citric acid is a weak organic acid that occurs naturally in citrus fruits. It is an intermediate in the citric acid cycle.

Name: Vancomycin
Information: Vancomycin is an antibiotic used to treat serious bacterial infections. It works by stopping the growth of bacteria.

Name: Sancycline
Information: Sancycline (Bonomycin, Norcycline, GS 2147) is a semi-synthetic tetracycline antibiotic.

Name: Cefazolin
Information: Cefazolin(Cephazolin) is a semisynthetic cephalosporin analog with broad-spectrum antibiotic action due to inhibition of bacterial cell wall synthesis. It attains high serum levels and is excreted quickly via the urine.

Name: Butenafine
Information: Butenafine is a synthetic benzylamine antifungal agent.

Name: Cefoxitin
Information: Cefoxitin is a beta-lactam, second-generation cephalosporin antibiotic with bactericidal activity.

Name: Doxycycline monohydrate
Information: Doxycycline is a synthetic, broad-spectrum tetracycline antibiotic exhibiting antimicrobial activity.

Name: L-Lactic acid
Information: L-Lactic acid is a natural product that is used as a food additive.,
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.

Name: Cyclohexanecarboxylic Acid
Information: Cyclohexanecarboxylic Acid, a component of the growth stimulant naphthenic acid, is the starting reagent for the synthesis of polyketide-type antibiotics, Phoslactomycins.
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.

Name: Chlorhexidine diacetate
Information: Chlorhexidine diacetate (Hibitane diacetate) is a disinfectant and topical anti-infective agent used also as mouthwash to prevent oral plaque.

Name: Tulobuterol hydrochloride
Information: Tulobuterol is a long-acting β2-adrenergic receptor agonist that has bronchodilatory, anti-inflammatory, and antiviral activities.

Name: Nimorazole
Information: Nimorazole is a water soluble, 5-nitroimidazole compound with antibacterial and potential radiosensitizing activity.

Name: Tildipirosin
Information: Tildipirosin is a 16-membered ring, tribasic and semi-synthetic macrolide antibiotic.

Name: KKL-35
Information: KKL-35 inhibits the trans-translation tagging reaction with an IC50 of 0.9 µM. It has broad-spectrum antibiotic activity.

Name: Embelin
Information: Embelin (Embelic Acid, NSC 91874), a quinone isolated from the Japanese Ardisia herb, is an inhibitor of X-linked inhibitor of apoptosis (XIAP) with IC50 of 4.1 μM in a cell-free assay.

Name: Brefeldin A
Information: Brefeldin A is a lactone antibiotic and ATPase inhibitor for protein transport with IC50 of 0.2 μM in HCT 116 cells, induces cancer cell differentiation and apoptosis. It could also improve the HDR(homology-directed repair) efficiency and be an enhancer of CRISPR-mediated HDR. Brefeldin A is also an inhibitor of autophagy and mitophagy.

Name: Anisomycin
Information: Anisomycin (Flagecidin, Wuningmeisu C) is a bacterial antibiotic isolated from Streptomyces griseolus, which inhibits protein synthesis, and also act as a JNK activator. Anisomycin upregulates autophagy and increases apoptosis.

Name: Ascomycin (FK520)
Information: Ascomycin (FK520, FR 900520, Immunomycin), an FK-506 analog, is a neutral macrolide immunosuppressant, which prevents rejection after an organ transplant. Phase 3.

Name: Puromycin (CL13900) 2HCl
Target: Antibiotics,Antineoplastic and Immunosuppressive Antibiotics,Selection Antibiotics for Transfected Cell
Information: Puromycin 2HCl (CL13900) is an aminonucleoside antibiotic, which acts as a protein synthesis inhibitor.

Name: Erythromycin Cyclocarbonate
Information: Erythromycin Cyclocarbonate(Davercin), derivative of Erythromycin, inhibits protein synthesis of bacteria by binding to the 50S ribosome.

Name: Fumagillin
Information: Fumagillin(Amebacilin,NSC9168) is a selective and potent irreversible inhibitor of Methionine aminopeptidase 2 (MetAP2), used as an antibiotic to treat microsporidiosis.

Name: 4-Hydroxytamoxifen (Afimoxifene)
Information: 4-Hydroxytamoxifen (Afimoxifene)  is the active metabolite of tamoxifen and a selective estrogen receptor (ER) modulator that is widely used in the therapeutic and chemopreventive treatment of breast cancer. It activates on-target modification frequency for intein-Cas9 variants.

Name: Ochromycinone (STA-21)
Information: Ochromycinone (STA-21) is a selective STAT3 inhibitor.

Name: Tubercidin
Information: Tubercidin (7-deaza-adenosine), an adenosine analogue, is a nucleoside antibiotic. It is incorporated into DNA and inhibits polymerases, thereby inhibiting DNA replication and RNA and protein synthesis. This agent also exhibits antifungal and antiviral activities.

Name: Omadacycline tosylate
Information: Omadacycline tosylate(PTK 0796 tosylate,Amadacycline tosylate) is a first-in-class aminomethylcycline antibiotic, demonstrating antimicrobial activity in vitro against a range of Gram-positive and Gram-negative aerobes and some anaerobic bacteria.

Name: Berberine
Information: Berberine (Umbellatine), an alkaloid isolated from Rhizoma coptidis, has broad applications, particularly as an antibacterial agent in the clinic.

Name: Berbamine
Information: Berbamine (BA), a traditional Chinese medicines extracted from Berberis amurensis (xiaoboan), is a novel inhibitor of bcr/abl fusion gene with potent anti-leukemia activity and also an inhibitor of NF-κB. Berbamine (BA) induces apoptosis in human myeloma cells and inhibits the growth of cancer cells by targeting Ca²⁺/calmodulin-dependent protein kinase II (CaMKII).

Name: Corylin
Information: Corylin, a main compound isolated from Psoralea corylifolia L. (Fabaceae), has a variety of pharmacological effects such as antioxidant, anti-proliferation, and anti-inflammatory properties.

Name: Ethyl palmitate
Information: Ethyl palmitate (Ethyl hexadecanoate, Palmitic acid ethyl ester) is a long-chain fatty acid ethyl ester that is used as a hair- and skin-conditioning agent.
DMSO (mM)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.
Synonyms: Ethyl hexadecanoate, Palmitic acid ethyl ester

Name: 10-Undecenoic acid
Information: 10-Undecenoic acid, a natural or synthetic fungistatic fatty acid, is used for the preparation of active pharmaceutical ingredients, cosmetics, perfumes, antidandruff shampoos and antimicrobial powders.
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.

Name: Josamycin
Information: Josamycin (EN-141, Kitasamycin A3, Leucomycin A3, Turimycin A5) is a macrolide antibiotic from Streptomyces narbonensis. The drug has antimicrobial activity against a wide spectrum of pathogens.
Synonyms: EN-141, Kitasamycin A3, Leucomycin A3, Turimycin A5

Name: Ozenoxacin
Information: Ozenoxacin(T-3912) is a quinolone antibiotic used for the treatment of impetigo.

Name: Pneumocandin B0
Information: Pneumocandin B0 (L-688786) is a natural product and a key intermediate in the synthesis of the antifungal agent.

Name: Ansamitocin p-3 (Maytansinol isobutyrate, NSC292222)
Information: Ansamitocin p-3 (Maytansinol isobutyrate, NSC292222, Antibiotic C 15003P3) is a potent inhibitor of tubulin polymerization with IC50 of 3.4 μM.

Name: Walrycin B
Information: Walrycin B is an antibacterial compound and a potent inhibitor of WalR targeting the WalR response regulator.

Name: Staurosporine (AM-2282)
Target: ADC Cytotoxin,Antineoplastic and Immunosuppressive Antibiotics,CaMK,PKA,PKC,PKG,S6 Kinase
Information: Staurosporine (AM-2282, Antibiotic AM-2282, STS) is a potent PKC inhibitor for PKCα, PKCγ and PKCη with IC50 of 2 nM, 5 nM and 4 nM, less potent to PKCδ (20 nM), PKCε (73 nM) and little active to PKCζ (1086 nM) in cell-free assays. Also shows inhibitory activities on other kinases, such as PKA, PKG, S6K, CaMKII, etc. Phase 3.

Name: (R)-3-Hydroxybutanoic acid
Information: (R)-3-Hydroxybutanoic acid (R-3HB, D-3-hydroxybutyric acid) is a monomer of PHB (poly[(R)-3-hydroxybutyrate]) with wide industrial and medical applications. (R)-3-hydroxybutyric acid can also serve as chiral precursor for synthesis of pure biodegradable PHB and its copolyesters.
DMSO (mg/mL)Max Solubility: The physical form of the compound is liquid, which can be dissolved in any proportion.

Name: Ceftaroline Fosamil
Information: Ceftaroline fosamil (CX-0903, DSP-5990, PPI-0903, TAK-599, Teflaro, Zinforo) is a cephalosporin with activity against Gram-positive pathogens, including methicillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus (MRSA).
Synonyms: CX-0903, DSP-5990, PPI-0903, TAK-599, Teflaro, Zinforo

Name: Pentostatin
Information: Pentostatin(CI-825,Deoxycoformycin) is a potent inhibitor of adenosine deaminase. The drug is effective in the treatment of many lymphoproliferative malignancies, particularly hairy-cell leukemia. It is also synergistic with some other antineoplastic agents and has immunosuppressive activity.

Name: Lefamulin acetate (Xenleta)
Information: Lefamulin acetate (Xenleta, BC-3781 acetate) is a pleuromutilin antibiotic for community-acquired bacterial pneumonia (CABP) treatment. Lefamulin acetate inhibits protein synthesis by binding to the peptidyl transferase center of the 50S bacterial ribosome, thus preventing the binding of transfer RNA for peptide transfer.

Name: Rifamycin S
Information: Rifamycin S, a quinone and an antibiotic against Gram-positive bacteria (including MRSA), is a clinical drug used to treat tuberculosis and leprosy. Rifamycin S generates reactive oxygen species (ROS) and inhibits microsomal lipid peroxidation.

Name: Pleuromutilin
Information: Pleuromutilin (Drosophilin B, Mutilin 14-glycolate), the lead compound for novel antibiotics, inhibits bacterial protein synthesis by binding to the 50S ribosomal subunit of bacteria.

Name: Delafloxacin Meglumine
Information: Delafloxacin (ABT-492, RX-3341, WQ-3034, Baxdela) meglumine is a broad-spectrum fluoroquinolone antibiotic against multiple pathogens.

Name: Tetracycline
Information: Tetracycline (TC) is a broad-spectrum antibiotic that exhibits activity against a wide range of microorganisms including gram-positive and gram-negative bacteria, chlamydiae, mycoplasmas, rickettsiae, and protozoan parasites.

Name: Oxacillin sodium
Information: Oxacillin sodium (salt) is a narrow-spectrum β-lactam antibiotic that can be used for treatment of methicillin-sensitive Staphylococcus aureus (MSSA) bacteremia.

Name: Procaine penicillin G
Information: Penicillin G Procaine (PGP, Penicillin G Procaine, Bicillin C-R), a crystalline complex combining penicillin G with procaine, is a β-lactam antibiotic.
Synonyms: PGP, Penicillin G Procaine, Bicillin C-R

Name: Ciprofloxacin hydrochloride
Information: Ciprofloxacin (CPX, Cetraxal, Ciloxan, Cipro, Bay-09867) hydrochloride, a fluorinated quinolone, is a β-diketone antibiotic with a broad spectrum antibacterial activity. Ciprofloxacin is an inhibitor of bacterial DNA gyrase (a subclass of Type II topoisomerases).
Synonyms: CPX, Cetraxal, Ciloxan, Cipro, Bay-09867 hydrochloride

Name: Cefpiramide
Information: Cefpiramide (Cefpiramide acid, Cefpiramido, Cefpiramidum, WY-44635, SM-1652) is a pseudomonas-active cephalosporin with a broad spectrum of antibacterial activity.
Synonyms: Cefpiramide acid, Cefpiramido, Cefpiramidum, WY-44635, SM-1652

Name: Oxytetracycline hydrochloride
Information: Oxytetracycline (OTC, Oxycycin, Stevacin, Terramycin) hydrochloride is a prescription antibiotic, interfering with the ability of bacteria to produce essential proteins.

Name: Cefodizime
Information: Cefodizime (CEF, CDZ) is an aminothiazolyl cephalosporin with a broad spectrum of antibacterial activity.

Name: Spectinomycin dihydrochloride pentahydrate
Information: Spectinomycin dihydrochloride pentahydrate (Trobicin) is a widely used antibiotic that inhibits bacterial protein synthesis by blocking translocation of messenger RNA and transfer RNAs on the ribosome.

Name: Ceftiofur sodium
Information: Ceftiofur sodium is a semisynthetic, beta-lactamase-stable, broad-spectrum cephalosporin with antibacterial activity.

Name: Ceftriaxone Sodium
Information: Ceftriaxone Sodium is the sodium salt form of ceftriaxone, a beta-lactam, third-generation cephalosporin antibiotic with bactericidal activity.

Name: Sulfathiazole sodium
Information: Sulfathiazole sodium, an antimicrobial agent, is an organosulfur compound that has been used as a short-acting sulfa drug.

Name: Dicloxacillin Sodium hydrate
Target: Antineoplastic and Immunosuppressive Antibiotics,Immunology & Inflammation related,P450 (e.g. CYP17)
Information: Dicloxacillin Sodium hydrate (DLX, Dycill, Dynapen, Pathocil), a narrow-spectrum β-Lactam antibiotic of the penicillin class, induces drug-metabolizing CYP enzymes to a clinically relevant extent.

Name: Amdinocillin
Information: Amdinocillin (Mecillinam, Coactin, FL 1060) is a β-lactam antibiotic with a broad spectrum of antibacterial activity. Amdinocillin is active alone against many gram-negative organisms.

Name: Chloroquine (NSC-187208)
Information: Chloroquine (NSC-187208, Aralen, CHQ, CQ) is an antimalarial drug and autophagy/lysosome inhibitor. Chloroquine also suppresses Toll-like receptor-9 (TLR9) protein expression. Chloroquine is highly effective agianst SARS-CoV-2 (COVID-19) infection with EC50 of 1.13 μM in Vero E6 cells. Chloroquine has anti-HIV-1 activity.

Name: Puromycin aminonucleoside
Information: Puromycin aminonucleoside (NSC 3056, PAN, Stylomycin aminonucleoside, ARDMA, SAN), the aminonucleoside portion of the antibiotic puromycin, is a reversible inhibitor of dipeptidyl-peptidase II and cytosol alanyl aminopeptidase that induces apoptosis in mesangial cells (MCs) accompanied by declined cell viability and enhanced inflammatory response.
Synonyms: NSC 3056, PAN, Stylomycin aminonucleoside, ARDMA, SAN

Name: 7-Methylcoumarin
Information: 7-Methylcoumarin can inhibit the growth of S. aureus and the growth of Gram-positive bacteria within a concentration of 0.8–3.6 μg/ml, and also has a strong hepatoprotective activity.

Name: Gemifloxacin mesylate
Information: Gemifloxacin mesylate (SB265805 mesylate; LB20304 mesylate) is a novel fluoronaphthyridone with a broad spectrum of antimicrobial activity and enhances activity against gram-positive aerobes.

Name: Oritavancin Diphosphate
Information: Oritavancin Diphosphate is an orally active glycopeptide antibiotic which is active against Gram-positive bacteria and also has antibacterial activity against multidrug-resistant Streptococcus pneumoniae.

Name: Doxorubicin
Information: Adriamycin (Doxorubicin, Hydroxydaunorubicin), a cytotoxic anthracycline antibiotic, is an anti-cancer chemotherapy agent, inhibits topoisomerase II with an IC50 of 2.67 μM, thus stopping DNA replication, and induces apoptosis, also inhibits human DNA topoisomerase I with an IC50 of 0.8 μM.

Name: Leptomycin B
Information: Leptomycin B (LMB, CI 940, Elactocin, Mantuamycin, NSC 364372) is a potent antifungal antibiotic isolated from Streptomyces and acts as a specific inhibitor of the nuclear export factor CRM1. Leptomycin B rapidly induces cytotoxic effects in cancer cell lines via covalent inhibition of CRM1 with IC50 values of 0.1 nM–10 nM.

Name: Biapenem
Information: Biapenem (L-627, LJC10627) is a carbapenem antibiotic with activity against both Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacterial strains.

Name: Mizoribine
Information: Mizoribine (Bredinin, NSC 289637,HE 69) is an imidazole nucleoside and an immunosuppressant that inhibits HCV RNA replication with IC50 of ~ 100 μM for anti-HCV activity. Mizoribine is a selective inhibitor of inosine-5'-monophosphate dehydrogenase (IMPDH) and guanosine monophosphate synthetase. Mizoribine also inhibits SARS-CoV.

Name: Polymyxin B sulphate
Target: Antibiotics,Antibiotics for Mammalian Cell Culture,Antineoplastic and Immunosuppressive Antibiotics
Information: Polymyxin B (Aerosporin, PMB, Poly-RX) is an antibiotic primarily used for resistant gram-negative infections.

Name: Teicoplanin
Information: Teicoplanin (Teichomycin,Targocid,MDL-507) is a glycopeptide antibiotic, used to treat serious infections caused by Gram-positive bacteria.

Name: D-Cycloserine
Information: D-cycloserine (RO-1-9213) is an analog of the amino acid D-alanine, used as an antibiotic in the treatment of tuberculosis.

Name: Clindamycin Phosphate
Information: Clindamycin Phosphate (NSC 618653) is a lincosamide antibiotic for Plasmodium falciparum with IC50 of 12 nM.

Name: Kanamycin sulfate
Target: Antibiotics,Antibiotics for Mammalian Cell Culture,Antibiotics for Plant Cell Culture,Selection Antibiotics for Transfected Cell
Information: Kanamycin sulfate (Kanamycin monosulfate, Ophtalmokalixan) is an aminoglycoside antibiotic, available in oral, intravenous, and intramuscular forms, and used to treat a wide variety of infections.

Name: Tobramycin
Information: Tobramycin (NSC 180514,Deoxykanamycin B, Nebramycin Factor 6) is an aminoglycoside antibiotic with an IC50 of 9.7 μM.

Name: Methacycline HCl
Information: Methacycline HCl (Rondomycin) is a tetracycline antibiotic, and also an inhibitor of epithelial–mesenchymal transition (EMT) with IC50 of roughly 5 μM, used to treat various infections.

Name: Lomefloxacin HCl
Information: Lomefloxacin HCl is a hydrochloride salt of lomefloxacin and is a fluoroquinolone antibiotic.

Name: Oxacillin sodium monohydrate
Information: Oxacillin sodium monohydrate (Methicillin) is an antibacterial agent and is a narrow spectrum beta-lactam antibiotic of the penicillin class.

Name: Neomycin sulfate
Target: Antibiotics,Antibiotics for Mammalian Cell Culture,Antineoplastic and Immunosuppressive Antibiotics,Bacterial,Selection Antibiotics for Transfected Cell
Information: Neomycin sulfate(Framycin sulfate) is an aminoglycoside antibiotic, used to treat bacteria infections.

Name: Streptomycin sulfate
Target: Antibiotics for Plant Cell Culture,Anti-infection,Selection Antibiotics for Transfected Cell
Information: Streptomycin sulfate(Phytomycin) is a sulfate salt of streptomycin that is a protein synthesis inhibitor.

Name: Vancomycin HCl
Information: Vancomycin HCl is a hydrochloride of vancomycin that is a narrow-spectrum glycopeptide antibacterial agent.

Name: Hygromycin B
Target: Antibiotics,Antibiotics for Plant Cell Culture,Antineoplastic and Immunosuppressive Antibiotics,Bacterial,Selection Antibiotics for Transfected Cell
Information: Hygromycin B (Hygrovetine), a selective antibiotic that is effective on most bacteria, fungi and higher eukaryotes, inhibits protein synthesis by interfering with translocation and causing mistranslation at the 70S ribosome.

Name: Zanamivir
Information: Zanamivir (GG167,GR 121167X) is a neuraminidase inhibitor used in the treatment and prophylaxis of influenza caused by influenza A virus and influenza B virus.

Name: Geneticin (G418 Sulfate)
Target: Antibiotics,Antibiotics for Plant Cell Culture,Antineoplastic and Immunosuppressive Antibiotics,Selection Antibiotics for Transfected Cell
Information: Geneticin (G418 Sulfate), an aminoglycoside antibiotic, is an elongation inhibitor of 80 S ribosomes that blocks polypeptide synthesis by inhibiting the elongation step in both prokaryotic and eukaryotic cells.

Name: Danofloxacin Mesylate
Information: Danofloxacin (CP-76136-27) is a fluoroquinolone antibacterial for veterinary use, with MIC90 of 0.28 μM.

Name: Amikacin disulfate
Information: Amikacin sulfate (BB-K8) binds to 16S rRNA (bacterial 30S ribosome), causing misreading of mRNA and supressing proteins synthesis.

Name: Caspofungin (MK-0991) Acetate
Information: Caspofungin Acetate (MK-0991, L-743872) is an lipopeptide antifungal β-1,3-glucan synthase inhibitor.

Name: Amikacin hydrate
Information: Amikacin(BAY416651 hydrate) is an aminoglycoside antibiotic used to treat different types of bacterial infections.

Name: Ceftazidime
Information: Ceftazidime(GR20263) is a third-generation cephalosporin that has activity against Gram-negative bacilli, including Pseudomonas aeruginosa.

Name: Penicillin V potassium salt
Information: Phenoxymethylpenicillin, also known as penicillin V, is an antibiotic useful for the treatment of a number of bacterial infections. It acts by inhibiting the biosynthesis of cell-wall peptidoglycan.

Name: Imipenem
Information: Imipenem acts as an inhibitor of AmpC β-lactamase and is an antibiotic useful for the treatment of a number of bacterial infections.

Name: Dexamethasone Sodium Phosphate
Information: Dexamethasone (Dexamethasone 21-phosphate disodium salt) is a potent synthetic member of the glucocorticoid class of steroid drugs, and an interleukin receptor modulator  that has anti-inflammatory and immunosuppressant effects.

Name: Colistin Sulfate
Information: Colistin (Polymixin E) is a cyclic cationic decapeptide linked to a fatty acid side chain, it belongs to a group of similarly structured bacterial antimicrobial peptides.

Name: Gentamicin Sulfate
Target: Antibiotics,Antibiotics for Mammalian Cell Culture,Antibiotics for Plant Cell Culture,Selection Antibiotics for Transfected Cell
Information: Gentamycin Sulfate (NSC-82261, SCH9724) is a broad-spectrum, aminoglycoside antibiotic used for cell culture which inhibits protein synthesis in sensitive organisms.

Name: Netilmicin Sulfate
Information: Netilmicin Sulfate is a member of the aminoglycoside family of antibiotics.

Name: Bismuth Subcitrate Potassium
Information: Bismuth Subcitrate is an antibiotic used to treat stomach ulcers associated with Helicobacter pylori, a bacterial infection.

Name: Tetramisole HCl
Information: Tetramisole(R-829,(±)-Tetramisole hydrochloride) is a mixture of dextro- and levo isomers used as an anthelmintic.

Name: Terbutaline Sulfate
Information: Terbutaline Sulfate(Terbutaline hemisulfate) is a selective β2-adrenergic receptor agonist with IC50 of 53 nM.

Name: Bacitracin
Information: Bacitracin is a mixture of related cyclic polypeptides produced by organisms of the licheniformis group of Bacillus subtilis var Tracy, which disrupts both gram positive and gram negative bacteria by interfering with cell wall and peptidoglycan synthesis.

Name: Chloroquine diphosphate
Information: Chloroquine diphosphate is a 4-aminoquinoline anti-malarial and anti-rheumatoid agent, also acting as an ATM activator. Chloroquine is also an inhibitor of toll-like receptors (TLRs).

Name: Ceftriaxone disodium salt hemi (heptahydrate)
Information: Ceftriaxone disodium salt hemi (heptahydrate) is a third-generation cephalosporin antibiotic.

Name: Paromomycin Sulfate
Target: Antibiotics,Antibiotics for Mammalian Cell Culture,Antibiotics for Plant Cell Culture,Selection Antibiotics for Transfected Cell
Information: Paromomycin Sulfate(Aminosidine sulfate) is an aminoglycoside antibiotics inhibiting protein synthesis in non-resistant cells by binding to 16S ribosomal RNA.

Name: Ribostamycin Sulfate
Information: Ribostamycin Sulfate(Vistamycin Sulfate,Landamycine) is an aminoglycoside antibiotic, containing a neutral sugar moiety, and is produced by Streptomyces ribosidiﬁcus.

Name: Capreomycin Sulfate
Information: Capreomycin Sulfate is a cyclic peptide antibiotic and thought to inhibit protein synthesis by binding to the 70S ribosomal unit.

Name: Apramycin Sulfate
Information: Apramycin Sulfate (Ai3-29795) is an aminoglycoside antibiotic, which binds to the deep groove of the RNA.

Name: Isepamicin Sulphate
Information: Isepamicin Sulphate (Isepamicine, Isepamycin, sch21420) is an aminoglycoside antibiotic, which inhibits bacterial protein synthesis by targeting the bacterial 30S ribosomal subunit.

Name: Micafungin (FK 463) Sodium
Information: Micafungin Sodium (FK463, Mycamine) is an inhibitor of 1, 3-beta-D-glucan synthesis, used as an antifungal drug.

Name: Ceftazidime Pentahydrate
Information: Ceftazidime is a β-lactam antibacterial agent which has demonstrated a broad spectrum of activity against Gram-positive and Gram-negative aerobic bacteria.

Name: Dihydrostreptomycin sulfate
Target: Antibiotics,Antibiotics for Mammalian Cell Culture,Bacterial,Selection Antibiotics for Transfected Cell
Information: Dihydrostreptomycin sulfate is an aminoglycoside antibiotic, used to treat bacterial diseases in cattle, pigs and sheep. Dihydrostreptomycin is a derivative of streptomycin.

Name: Sisomicin sulfate
Information: Sisomicin sulfate is an aminoglycoside antibiotic, isolated from the fermentation broth of a new species of the genus Micromonospora.

Name: Cefradine
Information: Cefradine (Cephradine, Sefril, Anspor, Velosef) is a semi-synthetic cephalosporin antibiotic.

Name: Fosfomycin Disodium
Information: Fosfomycin (Phosphonemycin) is a bactericidal, low-molecular weight, broad-spectrum antibiotic, with putative activity against several bacteria, including multidrug-resistant Gram-negative bacteria, by irreversibly inhibiting an early stage in cell wall synthesis.

Name: Pipemidic acid
Information: Pipemidic acid (Acido pipemidico) is a pyridopyrimidine antibiotic derivative of piromidic acid with activity against gram-negative and some gram-positive bacteria.

Name: Cephradine monohydrate
Information: Cefradine is a beta-lactam, first-generation cephalosporin antibiotic with bactericidal activity.

Name: Tobramycin sulfate
Information: Tobramycin sulfate is the sulfate salt of tobramycin, an aminoglycoside antibiotic derived from the bacterium Streptomyces tenebrarius with bactericidal activity.

Name: 2-Aminoisobutyric acid
Information: 2-Aminoisobutyric acid (NSC-16590, 2-Methylalanine, H-Aib-OH) is a rare, non-protein amino acid and end-product of pyrimidine metabolism, excreted in urine and found in some antibiotics of fungal origin.

Name: Blasticidin S HCl
Target: Antibiotics,DNA/RNA Synthesis,Selection Antibiotics for Transfected Cell
Information: Blasticidin S HCl is a nucleoside antibiotic isolated from Stretomyces girseochromogenes, and acts as a DNA and protein synthesis inhibitor, used to select transfected cells carrying bsr or BSD resistance genes.

Name: Citric acid trilithium salt tetrahydrate
Information: Citric acid trilithium salt tetrahydrate (Trilithium citrate tetrahydrate, Lithium citrate tribasic tetrahydrate) is a pharmaceutical and construction material. It is commonly used in HPLC gradient elution for quantification of amino acids.
Synonyms: Trilithium citrate tetrahydrate, Lithium citrate tribasic tetrahydrate

Name: Latamoxef sodium
Information: Latamoxef sodium (Moxalactam Disodium, FestamoxinLy, Shiomarin, Ly 127935, 6059 S) is an antibiotic and has anti-bacterial and anti-inflammation effects.
Synonyms: Moxalactam Disodium, FestamoxinLy, Shiomarin, Ly 127935, 6059 S

Name: 6-Diazo-5-oxo-L-norleucine
Information: 6-Diazo-5-oxo-L-norleucine (Diazooxonorleucine, L-6-Diazo-5-oxonorleucine, DON), an antibiotic isolated from Streptomyces, is a glutaminase antagonist with IC50 of ~1  mM for cKGA (kidney-type glutaminase). 6-Diazo-5-oxo-L-norleucine exhibits analgesic, antibacterial, antiviral and anticancer properties.

Name: Bekanamycin
Information: Bekanamycin is an aminoglycoside antibiotic.

Name: Amikacin Sulfate Salt
Information: Amikacin (BAY 41-6551) sulfate, a semisynthetic analog of kanamycin, is an aminoglycoside antibiotic which is very active against most gram-negative bacteria including gentamicin- and tobramycin-resistant strains.

Name: Dexamethasone phosphate disodium
Information: Dexamethasone phosphate disodium (DEX, Dexacort, Decadron, Dexair, Hexadrol, Maxidex) is a glucocorticoid receptor agonist with both anti-inflammatory and anti-oxidative effects.
Synonyms: DEX, Dexacort, Decadron, Dexair, Hexadrol, Maxidex, Dexamethasone 21-phosphate disodium salt

Name: Gatifloxacin hydrochloride
Information: Gatifloxacin (AM-1155, CG5501, BMS-206584, PD135432) hydrochloride is a potent fluoroquinolone antibiotic with broad-spectrum antibacterial activity. Gatifloxacin hydrochloride inhibits bacterial type II topoisomerases with IC50 of 13.8 μg/ml and 0.109 μg/ml for S. aureus topoisomerase IV and E. coli DNA gyrase, respectively.
Synonyms: AM-1155 hydrochloride, CG5501 hydrochloride, BMS-206584 hydrochloride, PD135432 hydrochloride

Name: Kasugamycin hydrochloride hydrate
Information: Kasugamycin (Ksg) hydrochloride hydrate, an antibiotic which binds both the 30S and 70S ribosome, specifically inhibits translation initiation of canonical but not of leaderless messenger RNAs.

Name: Gentamicin
Information: Gentamicin, an aminoglycoside class of bactericidal antibiotic, is effective against gram-negative bacterial infections.

Name: Framycetin sulphate
Information: Framycetin sulfate (Neomycin B sulfate), an aminoglycoside antibiotic, is a potent RNase P cleavage activity inhibitor with a Ki of 35 μM, and competes for specific divalent metal ion binding sites in RNase P RNA, also inhibits hammerhead ribozyme with a Ki of 13.5 μM.

Name: Colistin
Information: Colistin(Polymyxin E), a cyclic polypeptide antibiotic synthesized by Bacillus polymyxa subspecies colistinus Koyama, exerts antimicrobial activity by targeting at the bacterial cell membrane.

Name: Camptothecin (NSC-100880)
Information: Camptothecin (NSC-100880, CPT, Campathecin, (S)-(+)-Camptothecin) is a specific inhibitor of DNA topoisomerase I (Topo I) with IC50 of 0.68 μM in a cell-free assay. Camptothecin induces apoptosis in cancer cells via microRNA-125b-mediated mitochondrial pathways. Phase 2.

Name: Cefoselis Sulfate
Information: Cefoselis (FK 037 Sulfate) is a widely used beta-lactam antibiotic.

Name: Ofloxacin
Information: Ofloxacin (DL8280) is a synthetic broad-spectrum antimicrobial agent.

Name: Marbofloxacin
Information: Marbofloxacin is a potent antibiotic inhibiting bacterial DNA replication.

Name: Norfloxacin
Information: Norfloxacin (MK-0366) is a broad-spectrum antibiotic. Norfloxacin (MK-0366) targets bacterial gyrase and topoisomerase IV enzymes.

Name: Sulfapyridine
Information: Sulfapyridine  is a sulfonamide antibacterial.

Name: Sarafloxacin HCl
Information: Sarafloxacin HCl (A-56620) is a hydrochloride salt form of sarafloxacin which is a quinolone antibiotic drug with IC50 of 0.96 μg/L.

Name: Sitafloxacin Hydrate
Information: Sitafloxacin Hydrate (DU-6859a) is a new-generation, broad-spectrum oral fluoroquinolone antibiotic.

Name: Itraconazole (R 51211)
Information: Itraconazole (R 51211) is a relatively potent inhibitor of CYP3A4 with IC50 of 6.1 nM, used as a triazole antifungal agent. Itraconazole is a potent antagonist of the Hedgehog (Hh) signaling pathway. Itraconazole suppresses the growth of glioblastoma through induction of autophagy.

Name: 7-Aminocephalosporanic acid
Information: 7-Aminocephalosporanic acid is used for synthesis of cephalosporin antibiotics and intermediates.

Name: Enrofloxacin
Information: Enrofloxacin (BAY-Vp2674, PD160788) is a fluoroquinolone antibiotic.

Name: Cefadroxil hydrate
Information: Cefadroxil(BL-S 578 hydrate) is a broad-spectrum antibiotic of the cephalosporin type, effective in Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacterial infections.

Name: Clopidol
Information: Clopidol (WR 61112) is an antiprotozoal agent.

Name: Chlortetracycline HCl (NSC 13252)
Information: Chlortetracycline HCl (NSC 13252, 7-Chlorotetracycline, Aureomycin monohydrochloride) is the first identified tetracycline antibiotic.

Name: 6-Aminopenicillanic acid
Information: 6-Aminopenicillanic acid (6-APA) is the central component of penicillin β-lactam antibiotics which are generated by Penicillium. It is used as precursor for antibiotic compounds ampicillin and amoxicillin.

Name: Balofloxacin Dihydrate
Information: Balofloxacin Dihydrate is an orally active fluoroquinolone antibiotic.

Name: Sulfaquinoxaline sodium
Information: Sulfaquinoxaline sodium (N'1-quinoxalin-2-ylsulphanilamide sodium, SQ-Na) is the sodium salt of sulfaquinoxaline, which is often used as a drug to prevent coccidiosis in poultry, swine, and sheep by inhibiting the synthesis of nucleic acids and proteins in microorganisms.

Name: Cephalexin
Information: Cephalexin (Cefalexin) is an antibiotic that can treat a number of bacterial infections.

Name: Besifloxacin HCl
Information: Besifloxacin HCl is a fourth-generation fluoroquinolone antibiotic.

Name: Minocycline (CL 59806) HCl
Information: Minocycline (CL 59806,Minocin) HCl is the most lipid soluble and most active tetracycline antibiotic, binds to the 30S ribosomal subunit, preventing the binding of tRNA to the mRNA-ribosome complex and interfering with protein synthesis.
